<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="95" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,757,684,2069]" pageId="11" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,264,1818,1842]" pageId="11" pageNumber="95">Remarks:</emphasis>
We have improved the HOWARTH (1992) and BÉCAUD’ s (2006) diagnosis, because the finding of until unpublished samples from the Marconessa quarry have enlarged the genus variability.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,757,684,2069]" pageId="11" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,293,1948,1972]" pageId="11" pageNumber="95">Occurrence:</emphasis>
This genus characterizes the early Toarcian. It shows a considerable biodiversity over the time-span and a wide geographical dispersal, chiefly in the West Tethyan, Submediterranean and Suboreal Provinces.
</paragraph>
